Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Trim the @spring onion{1} and thinly slice. Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}. Zest and halve the @lime{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Slice lengthways into the @avocado{1}. Once you reach the stone turn the avocado around to cut it in half. Twist each half and pull it apart. Remove the stone then scoop out the flesh onto a #board{}. Chop into 2cm chunks.

Drain the @sweetcorn{150%g} in a #colander{} and pop in a #small bowl{}. Drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1} in a colander, pop half in another #bowl{} and mash with a #fork{} until nicely broken up. Put the spring onion, avocado, tomatoes and half the sweetcorn in a #large bowl{}. Squeeze in half the lime juice and add the @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix together, set aside.

> Use the ingredients listed for the exact amounts.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat. Once hot, add the @chorizo{120%g} and stir fry until starting to brown, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and @Mexican spice{1}(Mexican style spice mix), fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Add the @chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1}(finely chopped), kidney beans (whole and crushed), @beef stock powder{1} and remaining sweetcorn. Season with salt, pepper and a pinch of @sugar{pinch}, stir together and bring to the boil. Reduce the heat to medium, simmer until thick, ~{10-12%minutes}.

While the mixture cooks, pop the @soured cream{150%g} in a small bowl and add the lime zest. Season with salt and pepper and mix together. Set aside. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g} and break up the @feta cheese{100%g} into small chunks. Lay 1 @plain taco tortillas{6} per person on a #large baking tray{} lined with #baking paper{}. Once the tomato mixture is nicely thickened, remove from the heat.

Add a tablespoon of the chorizo mixture onto each taco on the baking tray and spread out with the back of the #spoon{}. Sprinkle over the cheddar and then cover with another taco. Repeat with another tbsp of chorizo mixture and the @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated) then top each stack with a third taco. Cover with the remaining chorizo mixture and spread over a spoonful of sour cream. Finish with the feta on top.

Bake in your oven until the feta is browned and the edges of the tacos golden, ~{8-10%minutes}. Once cooked, carefully place the stacks onto plates using a #spatula{}. Serve with the salsa spooned on top and a dollop of remaining sour cream. Enjoy!